================================================================================
HUNK 9 — Honest Holder Bridge Pool (off-chain claim window, no consensus diff)
================================================================================

The Bridge Pool is the part that makes the Restoration legitimate rather than
opportunistic: a 12-month window in which any holder of pre-attack OFF can
prove ownership and claim an equivalent balance on the restored chain. It is
intentionally implemented OFF-CHAIN — the Treasury multisig disburses by
signed transaction in response to verified claims — because:

  1) We don't have a complete pre-attack richlist snapshot (chainstate ends
     June 2015; attack was May 2018; the 3-year gap is partially reconstructable
     from zeewolfik/offerings + Wayback explorer snapshots but not authoritative
     enough to bake into chainparams).
  2) Consensus-level claim mechanisms are invasive; off-chain disbursement
     gives the Conclave room to verify edge cases (lost-then-recovered keys,
     compromised addresses, addresses descended from #699 attacker coins).
  3) The Treasury multisig already exists. Re-using it for Bridge claims is
     zero new infrastructure.

POOL SIZE
  1,500,000 OFF reserved at fork activation. Sized to cover:
    – ~10,000 OFF original genesis premine (block 1, scriptPubKey-locked,
       counted symbolically — those coins are unspendable already)
    – ~1,300,000 OFF of honest 2015-2018 mining rewards (estimated from
       870K blocks × 1.5 OFF average post-halving curve)
    – ~190,000 OFF buffer for forgotten/imperfectly-reconstructed balances

  The pool is NOT a separate UTXO with consensus enforcement. It is an
  ACCOUNTING reservation within the Conclave Treasury (P2SH 4fZqD…) plus
  a published cap. The Conclave commits to not disbursing more than 1.5M
  OFF for Bridge claims regardless of how many valid proofs arrive.

WINDOW
  Opens:  the day this announcement is posted to BCT 294383 (T0).
  Closes: T0 + 365 days (T0 + 12 months).
  Posted as an absolute UTC date in the BCT announcement post.
  At T0+1y any unclaimed remainder of the 1.5M reverts unconditionally to
  the Treasury — no further disbursement requests are honoured.

MANIFEST SOURCE — what counts as "provable pre-attack balance"

  IMPORTANT: When this section was first drafted we expected to verify
  claims against the v1.7 chainstate held in `zeewolfik/offerings` (BCT
  #698). On 2026-05-21 we discovered that repo is DELETED — ZeeWolf's
  GitHub account is alive but holds zero public repos, and the Wayback
  Machine has only one capture (2020-09-18) and only of the README index
  page. No raw checkpoints.cpp / chainparams.cpp / chainstate is
  preserved anywhere we can find. v1.7 source is functionally lost.

  The remaining authoritative source is the chainstate WE HAVE — the
  385 MB Wayback-recovered chainstate at block 966,413, June 2015,
  best-block hash 000000111e64c528... It is preserved at:
    primary host: ~/.Offering/blocks/ + chainstate/
    [BACKED UP TO SECONDARY HOST BEFORE FORK ACTIVATION — see deployment note]

  This means the Bridge manifest covers chain HISTORY UP TO BLOCK 966,413
  ONLY. Claims for addresses that received their first balance AFTER
  June 2015 (2015-2018 honest miners, Cryptopia withdrawal recipients,
  later p2p transfers) are NOT in our chainstate and cannot be cleanly
  verified.

CLAIM PROOF FORMAT

  Claimant must provide a `signmessage` proof from an OFF address.
  Verification rules differ by what the chainstate shows:

  Class A — Address present in our chainstate at block ≤ 966,413
    Provable. Conclave verifies the signature, looks up the address's
    UTXO balance at any point ≤ 966,413, and approves up to that
    balance. Address must NOT be in the #699 banned list. This class
    covers chain genesis through June 2015 — the well-documented
    period.

  Class B — Address NOT present in our chainstate (post-2015 only)
    Discretionary. Claimant must provide:
      (a) signmessage proof from the address;
      (b) a credible story of how the address came to hold OFF (mining
          payout from pool X on date Y; Cryptopia withdrawal; p2p tip
          from named person; ritual special-block win at height H);
      (c) any corroborating evidence the Conclave can sanity-check
          against the BCT thread, archived Cryptopia pages, or other
          remembered community accounting.
    Default cap for Class B claims: 1,000 OFF per address, regardless
    of claimed balance. Larger Class B claims require Conclave vote
    in-thread before disbursement, with the reasoning posted publicly.
    Small-holder doubt benefit; large-holder evidence burden.

  All claims, in either class:
    – Address MUST NOT be in the #699 banned list (the 8 from vampirus).
    – Address MUST NOT be the direct recipient of a transaction whose
      input traces back to a #699 address (1-hop laundering check;
      we don't chase further than that).

  Challenge string the claimant signs (the Conclave will rotate this weekly
  on a published schedule to prevent replay):
    "Conclave-Restoration-Bridge-<YYYYMMDDw>-<address>-<claim-amount-in-OFF>"
    e.g.  "Conclave-Restoration-Bridge-20260521w-Q…xY-15.5"
  Format: literal label, ISO-week tag, claimant address, claim amount.

  Claimant posts to BCT 294383 in this exact format:
    [code]
    Claim: <historical-address>
    Amount: <amount-OFF>
    Signature: <base64 signmessage output>
    New-chain destination: <new OFF address you control>
    [/code]

  The Conclave verifies the signature with `Offerings-cli verifymessage`,
  checks the address+balance against the historical snapshot manifest,
  and either confirms (+ disburses) or contests (+ explains) in-thread
  within 7 days of the claim post. All claims and verifications are
  permanently archived in the BCT thread.

DISBURSEMENT MECHANICS

  Verified claims are batched into multisig transactions roughly weekly.
  The Conclave produces a partial-signed transaction (Key #1 sigs all
  pending claims), passes it to Key #2 (second signature), and broadcasts.
  Key #3 (paper-cold) is NEVER touched for routine Bridge disbursement —
  it is the disaster-recovery key, not an operational one.

  Each batch is announced in-thread with:
    – list of claims included (claimant -> amount -> destination)
    – txid of the resulting multisig spend
    – running Bridge Pool remainder

CLOSING

  At T0 + 13 months the Conclave posts a final accounting:
    – total Bridge claims approved
    – total Bridge claims contested
    – Bridge Pool remainder reverting to Treasury
    – running Treasury balance + outstanding spend authority

EDGE CASES & POLICY (publish with the BCT post for transparency)

  1) Address that received coinbase rewards from honest mining 2015-2018:
       claimable for full historical balance, capped at 50,000 OFF per
       address (largest documented honest stack in the thread was 50K
       per msg #451). Cap prevents a single archived miner from claiming
       a Top-10 richlist position.

  2) Address that received Cryptopia withdrawals 2015-2018:
       claimable per signed message; balance proven via historical
       chainstate (zeewolfik snapshot) at time of last withdrawal.

  3) Address commingled with attacker UTXOs after May 2018:
       contested. Claimant may provide evidence of innocent acquisition
       (purchase from Cryptopia order book, mining payout, etc.). Conclave
       decides in good faith and posts reasoning in-thread.

  4) Address claimed by multiple parties:
       first valid signature wins. Subsequent claimants must prove the
       prior signer is themselves (highly unlikely to come up in practice).

  5) Lost keys / damaged wallet.dat:
       not claimable. The Bridge requires a `signmessage` proof, which
       requires the private key. There is no recovery path for genuinely
       lost keys — this matches the original chain's economics.

  6) Original developer keys (Blazr2, HagbardCeline, etc.):
       claimable in-full, no cap. The Conclave will publicly affirm
       these claims and post them at the top of the Bridge ledger.

NOTE TO FUTURE CONCLAVE

  After T0 + 13 months, the 1.5M reservation is dissolved. Any further
  pre-attack-holder claims after that date are at the Conclave's
  discretion and come out of the general Treasury, NOT a dedicated pool.
  Be generous within reason; the goal is to close the social-contract
  gap, not to litigate it.

